  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">EHF WASH Response to Cholera Affected Communities in South Omo, Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project plans to increase the coverage of clean water, hand washing facilities, sanitation and hygiene services to reduce potential risks of fatalities and contain the spread of cholera outbreak in four woredas of South Omo Zone. Major activities include: 
&#x2022; Rehabilitation 28 non-functional water schemes and 2 pipe line extensions from existing water schemes with construction of additional water points,

&#x2022; Construction of 12 semi-permanent latrines, construction of 26 wash basins and provision of handwashing facilities at health centres, schools, CTCs and other public places, 
&#x2022; Enhancing awareness of communities to control and prevent the cholera outbreak and COVID-19,

&#x2022; Provision of WASH NFIs (soaps) and water purification tabs,
&#x2022; Setting up and support community rehydration centres, 
&#x2022; Provision of COVID-19 prevention materials for distribution team (staffs and volunteers) - masks, glove and hand sanitizer,
&#x2022; Post distribution monitoring.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The prevalence/impacts of water-borne diseases/cholera is reduced in the Bena Tsemay, Male, Selamago and Semen Ari woredas and surrounding areas; Access of the population to drinking water in the four woredas and surrounding areas is improved; Sanitation services are improved; The proportion of the population sensitized and who have positively changed their behaviour towards hygiene and health has increased;</narrative>
  </description>
